Everyone, run!

168
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,960
Heh, you're late...

169
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,740
I got tired of waiting.

170
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,840
Too bad,

171
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:02,890
but I've taken care of all of 
the resistance members.

172
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,080
I, the great Shura!

173
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:09,660
You're Night Raid?

174
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:12,130
You'll entertain me at least a little, right?

175
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:15,630
Hmm? Oh?

176
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:18,230
You're the one who was with Esdeath,

177
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:21,140
when I transported her to the far island.

178
00:10:22,290 --> 00:10:25,640
That means you were behind 
all those Danger Beasts.

179
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,640
What was the point?

180
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:29,860
Isn't it obvious?

181
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,770
Because it was fun!

182
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:36,180
I despise boredom.

183
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:39,490
I had a lot of fun on their behalf.

184
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:42,420
How dare you?!

185
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,420
Tatsumi!

186
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,290
Wh-What is this?

187
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,840
As I suspected, some rats snuck in.

188
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:05,700
Hey! You came at a good 
time, Old Man Lightning.

189
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,710
I'll leave them to you.

190
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:09,730
I don't need you to tell me.

191
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,030
My name is Budou.

192
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:16,820
I've been appointed Commander-in-Chief 
by our lord and master.

193
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:19,400
<i>So this is the Commander-in-Chief.</i>

194
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:22,410
With your treasonous acts, 
you've wronged the empire.

195
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:26,110
Your fate will be determined by my Imperial Arms,

196
00:11:26,110 --> 00:11:29,040
Thunder God's Rage: Adramelech.

197
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,550
Tatsumi!

198
00:11:38,940 --> 00:11:40,350
Crap...

199
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,650
I wasn't even hit.

200
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:42,840
What was that impact?

201
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:46,560
Oh, so you dodged my attack.

202
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,600
You've got a good eye.

203
00:11:49,690 --> 00:11:52,690
<i>Incursio!</i>

204
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,690
Tatsumi!

205
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:08,410
What the hell? When did you...

206
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,700
I'll be your opponent.

207
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:13,040
Make sure you guys don't interfere.

208
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,750
This one's my prey.

209
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,880
That was fun.

210
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:25,290
Clearly, I am better suited to a 
battlefield than to guard duty.

211
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:36,230
We're heading back to the capital.

212
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:40,510
<i>You had best prepare yourselves, Night Raid.</i>

213
00:12:46,410 --> 00:12:47,250
What?

214
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:49,660
Pay attention, Night Raid!

215
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,750
Oh? An Imperial Arms made of string.

216
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,440
That's pretty interesting.

217
00:12:58,380 --> 00:13:02,590
Don't look so surprised. 
I'll reveal the trick to my Imperial Arms.

218
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:09,180
My toy, Shambhala, 
can teleport me or anyone else,

219
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:12,960
so long as I've marked the location.

220
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:16,270
<i>An Imperial Arms that controls time and space.</i>

221
00:13:16,470 --> 00:13:21,070
It's extremely tiring, so I wasn't able 
to constantly attack before.

222
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:27,240
But I got my hands on 
something great in the capital.

223
00:13:28,610 --> 00:13:31,980
Now I can teleport as much as I want.

224
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:37,670
As you can see, I've marked a 
lot of places in the palace!

225
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:43,840
What's wrong? You aren't gonna run?

226
00:13:48,830 --> 00:13:51,390
Hey, hey, are we done already?

227
00:13:52,110 --> 00:13:53,950
<i>There's no point in trying to get away.</i>

228
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:56,770
<i>No matter where I go, 
he'll reach me immediately!</i>

229
00:13:57,210 --> 00:13:58,250
<i>But...</i>

230
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:02,270
<i>He won't be able to get to me 
in an area he hasn't marked.</i>

231
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:05,210
Huh?

232
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:12,720
That's too bad.

233
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:15,080
You can leave a mark in the air?

234
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:17,320
Exactly.

235
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:20,250
From the start, there was 
nowhere for you to run.

236
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,500
Nowhere.

237
00:14:30,430 --> 00:14:34,090
<i>He may be strong, but his moves 
leave openings. I can do it.</i>

238
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:47,550
Young man, what is your name?

239
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:48,350
Huh?

240
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:49,410
Your name...

241
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,890
Unless assassins don't have names.

242
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:54,120
It's Tatsumi.

243
00:14:54,490 --> 00:14:55,730
<i>Tatsumi?</i>

244
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,860
<i>How earnest.</i>

245
00:14:57,860 --> 00:14:59,440
<i>How honest.</i>

246
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:02,890
<i>There isn't a single tremor 
in his swordsmanship.</i>

247
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:08,800
<i>How much discipline does one 
need to become this skilled?</i>

248
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:09,800
<i>However...</i>

249
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:17,270
<i>If you've wronged the 
empire or His Excellency,</i>

250
00:15:17,670 --> 00:15:20,190
<i>I must destroy you!</i>

251
00:15:30,010 --> 00:15:31,180
Tatsumi!

252
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:33,470
You...

253
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:34,310
I'm sorry.

254
