00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:03,440
Eventually, I'll surpass my father, 
and the very throne will be mine.

265
00:16:05,090 --> 00:16:07,740
Hey, don't tell me you're giving up.

266
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,820
We aren't done playing.

267
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:12,020
No, we're done.

268
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:13,570
You lose.

269
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:14,480
Huh?

270
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:23,420
Commander Shura!

271
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,420
Don't move.

272
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:26,710
Or I'll cut off more than 
just his arm next time.

273
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,540
You...

274
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:30,550
What's this?

275
00:16:30,550 --> 00:16:32,600
It's a barrier made of my thread.

276
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:37,220
I used almost all of it.
 I just barely made it.

277
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:40,100
You did this while you were running around?

278
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:46,150
Thanks to your showing off, 
I figured out where all the marks were.

279
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,670
You little bastard...

280
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:50,230
Now, everyone drop your weapons!

281
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:54,110
Shura, there are many questions I want to ask.

282
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,910
Y-You...

283
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:05,800
M-Master Shura, please take this into account.

284
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:09,230
And free my father... And my mother...

285
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:21,310
Too bad! Your parents were 
killed a long time ago!

286
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:24,520
Thanks for showing me a good time, Night Raid.

287
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:28,600
However, it's about time to end this.

288
00:17:28,980 --> 00:17:32,490
I'll let you have a taste of my hidden ability.

289
00:17:33,650 --> 00:17:37,090
Disappear! Off the face of the world!

290
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:51,170
No one's ever come back 
from this hidden ability.

291
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:56,050
Crumble into dust in the abyss, Night Raid!

292
00:17:57,110 --> 00:17:57,890
Huh?

293
00:17:58,550 --> 00:17:59,640
<i>String?</i>

294
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:02,640
<i>Don't tell me... That son of a bitch!</i>

295
00:18:02,930 --> 00:18:06,920
Regardless of who you who are, 
you can't sever this thread,

296
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:10,400
even if you have an Imperial Arms that 
can manipulate time and space.

297
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,970
So we meet again.

298
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:17,280
You...

299
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,660
Like I'd let you escape!

300
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,380
Don't give me that look...

301
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,790
Let's go together, Mister Shura.

302
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:30,810
You've gotta be joking...

303
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:32,930
I can't die here.

304
00:18:32,930 --> 00:18:37,420
I need the throne, so I can 
change this boring world!

305
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:41,760
It isn't like I don't understand what you want.

306
00:18:42,740 --> 00:18:46,090
Crap, I can't... In a place like this...

307
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:47,270
I was supposed to...

308
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:50,040
You want to change the world, huh?

309
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:54,420
I understand. Everyone feels that way...

310
00:18:55,630 --> 00:19:01,290
But it doesn't give you the right to 
treat others' lives like toys.

311
00:19:01,290 --> 00:19:03,990
You can't just destroy whatever you want!

312
00:19:27,090 --> 00:19:29,620
We've been through a lot,

313
00:19:30,290 --> 00:19:32,190
Cross Tail...

314
00:19:44,130 --> 00:19:46,760
Miss Najenda, I'm sorry.

315
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,950
It seems like this is it for me...

316
00:19:51,170 --> 00:19:53,880
I'll leave the rest to you, Tatsumi.

317
00:20:10,830 --> 00:20:11,680
Lu...

318
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:13,980
Lubba...

319
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:18,300
Lubba!

320
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:25,400
D-D-Died?

321
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:31,200
No, Shura!

322
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:35,460
To think you've left me!

323
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,540
Oh, well.

324
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:41,210
Nothing to be done about his death.

325
00:20:41,210 --> 00:20:47,090
At least he was able to finish off 
one of the Night Raid members.

326
00:20:47,550 --> 00:20:51,860
The other one is confined in the dungeon.

327
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:53,230
Good work.

328
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:55,290
Now, then...

329
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:59,440
We need to make an example out of him.

330
00:20:59,890 --> 00:21:03,890
So the Revolutionary Army knows to back down.

331
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:09,280
Now, I wonder what awful things 
we should do to him...

332
00:21:13,290 --> 00:21:15,890
Boorish as always.

333
00:21:15,890 --> 00:21:21,710
But it would be successful in discouraging traitors.

334
00:21:23,580 --> 00:21:25,550
I heard what happened, Budou.

335
00:21:26,130 --> 00:21:28,260
Give that role to me.

336
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:29,850
Oh?

337
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,340
<i>Tatsumi...</i>

338
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:34,320
<i>I won't let anyone else have you.</i>

339
00:21:48,490 --> 00:21:51,450
To be executed in public...

340
00:21:52,630 --> 00:21:54,790
Tatsumi...

341
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:40,980
Kill the Despair

342
00:23:40,980 --> 00:23:42,980


